timeline.bodyText:
Optional offers functional semantics to express the same without explicit checks and for a more fluent syntax. eg.:
 public static String getTitle(@NonNull Optional<Feature> feature) {
   return getCaption(feature).orElseGet(() -> getLayerName(feature));
  }

  private static Optional<String> getCaption(@NonNull Optional<Feature> feature) {
    return feature.map(Feature::getCaption).filter(caption -> !caption.trim().isEmpty());
  }

  private static String getLayerName(@NonNull Optional<Feature> feature) {
    return feature.map(Feature::getLayer).map(Layer::getName).orElse("");
  }

This also avoids needing to remember to check isPresent(), and the get() syntax to unpack the optional.

